result.execSummary:
The defendant Jeffrey A David was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Marquette County DNA Proof of Submission

Defendant Jeffrey A David in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee moves to amend Ct 1 to Disorderly Conduct, contrary to 947.01(1) - a class B Misd.  Court questions defendant.  BY THE COURT:  Court approves the amendment.  Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Atty Gumz agrees.  Defendant enters a No Contest plea to the amended charges.  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of the amended Ct 1.
Atty Gumz makes sentencing statement.  Defendant makes statement.
BY THE COURT:  Sentence withheld, defendant placed on probation for a period of 12 months.  Conditions:  *Serve 10 days in the Marquette County Jail with huber.  Sentence to commence by 6/9/17 at 7:00pm.  Report clean & sober.  *Pay costs of $243.00.  *Submit DNA sample and pay surcharge of $200.00.  *Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent.  *Bond on file to be applied to costs and the balance to be paid during the period of probation.
